
test_concurrent: Perform a KDC, a PKE, a DMAC and a SIC operation concurrently

The cores are open and polled in a cmrt_sic_wait loop.
Before the poll loop, a sic receive operation is started. When a sic message
arrives it is handled inside the loop and echoes back. This handling also
triggers the remaining operations (one per core). When all operations finish,
the test exits.

The return code is written to SIC register SCRATCH_0 before exiting the
container. A value of 0 means success.

The container can be run in TESTED or PROVISIONED or MISSION lifecycle.

To run (load and start) container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 run test_concurrent.img

Any sic message will trigger all functions to be launched in a wait loop:
$ cmtest data -f100 "Run tests"
-- The message should be echoed back.

When the container has exited (use mwtest.py ps to check for flowid 100),
the return code can be read from SIC:
$ cmrt sic R_SCRATCH_0

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
